</section></div>
</div></section></div><div data-type=3D"example" id=3D"element-807" class=
=3D"ui-has-child-title"><header><h2 class=3D"os-title">
  <span class=3D"os-title-label">Example </span>
  <span class=3D"os-number">4.12</span>
  <span class=3D"os-divider"> </span>
</h2></header><section>
<div class=3D"body">
<p id=3D"element-175">Approximately 70% of statistics students do their hom=
ework in time for it to be collected and graded. Each student does homework=
 independently. In a statistics class of 50 students, what is the probabili=
ty that at least 40 will do their homework on time? Students are selected r=
andomly.<span data-type=3D"newline" data-count=3D"2"><br><br></span></p><di=
v data-type=3D"exercise" id=3D"element-1751" class=3D"unnumbered has-proble=
m-title"><header></header><section><div data-type=3D"problem" id=3D"id53170=
83"><h3 data-type=3D"problem-title">
  <span class=3D"os-title-label">Problem</span>
</h3>
<div class=3D"os-problem-container">
<p id=3D"element-732">a. This is a binomial problem because there is only a=
 success or a __________, there are a fixed number of trials, and the proba=
bility of a success is 0.70 for each trial.</p>
<p id=3D"element-73124">b. If we are interested in the number of students w=
ho do their homework on time, then how do we define <em data-effect=3D"ital=
ics">X</em>?</p>
<p id=3D"element-732324">c. What values does <em data-effect=3D"italics">x<=
/em> take on?</p>
<p id=3D"element-7324">d. What is a "failure," in words?</p>
<p id=3D"element-74">e. If <em data-effect=3D"italics">p</em> + <em data-ef=
fect=3D"italics">q</em> =3D 1, then what is <em data-effect=3D"italics">q</=
em>?</p>
<p id=3D"element-70">f. The words "at least" translate as what kind of ineq=
uality for the probability question <em data-effect=3D"italics">P</em>(<em =
data-effect=3D"italics">x</em> ____ 40).</p>

</div></div>
<details data-type=3D"solution" id=3D"id5321627" aria-label=3D"Show/Hide So=
lution">
        <summary class=3D"btn-link ui-toggle" title=3D"Show/Hide Solution" =
data-content=3D"Show/Hide Solution"></summary>
        <section class=3D"ui-body" role=3D"alert"><h3 data-type=3D"solution=
-title">
  <span class=3D"os-title-label">Solution</span>
</h3>
<div class=3D"os-solution-container">
 <p id=3D"element-23523">a. failure</p>
 <p id=3D"element-235352">b. <em data-effect=3D"italics">X</em> =3D the num=
ber of statistics students who do their homework on time<span data-type=3D"=
newline" data-count=3D"2"><br><br></span></p>
 <p id=3D"element-23352">c. 0, 1, 2, =E2=80=A6, 50<span data-type=3D"newlin=
e" data-count=3D"2"><br><br></span></p>
 <p id=3D"element-232">d. Failure is defined as a student who does not comp=
lete their homework on time.</p>
<p id=3D"element-8865">The probability of a success is <em data-effect=3D"i=
talics">p</em> =3D 0.70. The number of trials is <em data-effect=3D"italics=
">n</em> =3D 50.<span data-type=3D"newline" data-count=3D"2"><br><br></span=
></p>
 <p id=3D"element-5352">e. <em data-effect=3D"italics">q</em> =3D 0.30<span=
 data-type=3D"newline" data-count=3D"2"><br><br></span></p>
 <p id=3D"element-23532">f. greater than or equal to (=E2=89=A5)
<span data-type=3D"newline" data-count=3D"1"><br></span>The probability que=
stion is <em data-effect=3D"italics">P</em>(<em data-effect=3D"italics">x</=
em> =E2=89=A5 40).</p></div>
</section>
      </details>
</section></div></div></section></div>



